# AAEP CODEOWNERS
#
# This file defines who automatically gets review requests for changes in
# specific parts of the repository. See:
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Bootstrap period: a single Maintainer reviews everything. As more
# Maintainers join (per GOVERNANCE.md §2.6), this file will route reviews
# to subject-matter owners.
#
# Format: <path pattern>  @owner1 @owner2 ...

# Global default — every PR gets this reviewer if no more-specific rule matches
*                                       @Ramseyxlil

# Specification — highest review bar; affects every implementation
/spec/                                  @Ramseyxlil
/schemas/                               @Ramseyxlil

# Conformance suite — changes here change what "conformant" means
/conformance/                     @Ramseyxlil

# Governance — changes affect community structure
/governance/                            @Ramseyxlil
/governance/proposals/                  @Ramseyxlil

# Security policy — handled by the security team only
